            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Text from autopsy</note></app>
                <app loc="line 2"><note>Final character is not clearly an I (as read by Manganaro) but could also be N, although the most visible diagonal is superficial damage</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 3"><note>The π has a second horizontal stroke at the midpoint; a short vertical stroke is visible at the right-hand edge of the stone</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p><!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div--></p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Rediscovered in the Museum stores in 2014, having not been seen since initial publication by Manganaro. Inventory number not yet identified. The text looks rather later than the Hellenistic date proposed by Manganaro, who published it in the context of the Hellenistic oracular verse texts from Akrai, and seems more likely to be of the Roman imperial period.</p>
            </div>
